.TH SSHTO "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sshto \- Menu-driven SSH client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sshto
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,HOST\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sshto
is a menu-driven SSH client that provides an interactive interface for managing and connecting to SSH hosts. It reads from your SSH config and provides a searchable menu.
.PP
The script simplifies SSH connection management with a user-friendly interface.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sshto
Launch interactive SSH menu
.TP
.B sshto webserver
Connect to host named webserver
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/sshto/settings.conf
User configuration file for sshto preferences
.TP
.B ~/.ssh/config
SSH configuration file (hosts are read from here)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Reads hosts from ~/.ssh/config
.IP \(bu 2
Menu-driven selection
.IP \(bu 2
Supports search and filtering
